The paper deals with a unified framework for tying overlapping meshes in solid mechanics applications, which involves the use of numerical methods and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MS (Mathematical Software), which deals with the development and analysis of algorithms and software for mathematical computations. 

The paper also involves the use of numerical methods for solving partial differential equations, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). 

The paper deals with the application of the proposed framework to solid mechanics problems, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). 

The paper also involves the use of Lagrange multipliers, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering). 

Finally, the paper deals with the problem of mesh tying along embedded interfaces, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.EM (Engineering Mechanics).
